Sassa says beneficiaries should avoid collecting their grants on the first day of payment. JOHANNESBURG – The coronavirus (COVID-19) outbreak is also impacting social grant payments. The Social Security Agency (Sassa) says beneficiaries should avoid collecting their grants on the first day of payment. This is aimed at preventing large gatherings at grant payment points like post offices. “We will ensure we don’t have 100 people or more at the Post Office at a time. We will tighten security.” To track the latest developments around the coronavirus both in South Africa and abroad, click on this live status report from Strategix.